OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FThefts of historic stone   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fand metal rise - report    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Thefts of historic stone and metal are 
OL,6, on the rise, according to a new report 
OL,7, by Historic England and the National   
OL,8, Police Chiefs' Council.                
OL,10,FIt sets out how walls and paving slabs 
OL,11,Fwere stolen in Yorkshire and Cheshire, 
OL,12,Fwhile granite troughs and fountains    
OL,13,Fwere taken in Kent and London.         
OL,15,FMeanwhile, metal thefts from church    
OL,16,Froofs were particularly common during  
OL,17,Fthe Covid lockdowns, the report added. 
OL,19,FHistoric England said such thefts "rob 
OL,20,Fus of our collective history".         
